title.narrative: STRENGTHENING INSTITUTIONS AND PROFESSIONALS

description.narrative: Specialized institutions and professionals have increased capacities to provide comprehensive protection to children and adolescents in prioritized territories and groups in conditions of violence and other social vulnerabilities., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Evaluation, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, more girls, boys and adolescents from prioritized groups and territories benefit from comprehensive, violence-free prevention and protection services and areas.

title.narrative: Specialized institutions and professionals have increased capacities to provide comprehensive protection to children andadolescents in prioritized territories and groups in conditions of violence and other social vulnerabilities.

description.narrative: Two indicators related to the strengthening of capacities of institutions and professionals to provide protection to children and adolescents were fulfilled. The training actions reached 1,521 professionals who acquired knowledge and tools associated to the right of children and adolescents to a violence-free life and its relation with the changes in legal regulations underway in Cuba. Although the third indicator could not be fulfilled due to the limitations of mobility imposed by COVID-19, 4 tools were developed for work with children and adolescents without family care. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:14/01/2022
